      "source": [
        "## **Data Cleaning and Pre-processing**\n",
        "\n",
        "Before analysis, the dataset is cleaned by:\n",
        "1. Handling missing or null values\n",
        "2. Converting time variables into proper datetime format\n",
        "3. Sorting the dataset chronologically\n",
        "4. Removing duplicates if present\n",
        "5. Proper preprocessing improves model accuracy and ensures reliable visualisations."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 30,
      "id": "6d94b797-e51b-43cd-ab96-c43c7cba6894",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6d94b797-e51b-43cd-ab96-c43c7cba6894"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Changing the data types\n",
        "# 1. Correcting data types for the float columns\n",
        "float_cols = [\n",
        "    'Avg_Temp (°C)', 'Max_Temp (°C)', 'Min_Temp (°C)',\n",
        "    'Precipitation (mm)', 'Humidity (%)', 'Wind_Speed (m/s)',\n",
        "    'Solar_Irradiance (W/m²)', 'Cloud_Cover (%)', 'CO2_Concentration (ppm)',\n",
        "    'Latitude', 'Longitude', 'Altitude (m)', 'Proximity_to_Water (km)',\n",
        "    'Urbanization_Index', 'Vegetation_Index', 'ENSO_Index',\n",
        "    'Particulate_Matter (µg/m³)', 'Sea_Surface_Temp (°C)'\n",
        "]\n",
        "climate_data[float_cols] = climate_data[float_cols].apply(pd.to_numeric, errors='coerce')\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. For the 'Year' and 'Month' columns\n",
        "time_cols = ['Year', 'Month']\n",
        "for col in time_cols:\n",
        "    climate_data[col] = pd.to_numeric(climate_data[col], errors='coerce').astype('Int64')\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. Converting Location/Index data to Floats\n",
        "geography = [\n",
        "    'Latitude', 'Longitude', 'Altitude (m)', 'Proximity_to_Water (km)',\n",
        "    'Urbanization_Index', 'Vegetation_Index'\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4. Applying the conversion to all measurement and geography columns\n",
        "measurements = [\n",
        "    'Avg_Temp (°C)', 'Max_Temp (°C)', 'Min_Temp (°C)', 'Precipitation (mm)',\n",
        "    'Humidity (%)', 'Wind_Speed (m/s)', 'Solar_Irradiance (W/m²)',\n",
        "    'Cloud_Cover (%)', 'CO2_Concentration (ppm)', 'Sea_Surface_Temp (°C)',\n",
        "    'ENSO_Index', 'Particulate_Matter (µg/m³)'\n",
        "]\n",
        "all_numeric = measurements + geography\n",
        "climate_data[all_numeric] = climate_data[all_numeric].apply(pd.to_numeric, errors='coerce')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Fill any remaining NA values in 'Year' before converting to non-nullable int\n",
        "climate_data['Year'] = climate_data['Year'].ffill().bfill()\n",
        "# Ensure all NA values are filled with a reasonable default, like the median year, before converting to non-nullable int\n",
        "climate_data['Year'] = climate_data['Year'].fillna(climate_data['Year'].median())\n",
        "climate_data['Year'] = climate_data['Year'].astype(int)"
      ]
    },
